Uses EIP-2935's history storage contract which maintains a ring buffer of the last 8191 block hashes in state. For blocks within the last 256 blocks, it uses the native `BLOCKHASH` opcode. For blocks between 257 and 8191 blocks ago, it queries the EIP-2935 history storage. For blocks older than 8191 or future blocks, it returns zero, matching the `BLOCKHASH` behavior. NOTE: After EIP-2935 activation, it takes 8191 blocks to completely fill the history.
